Money Tree (Multiple Sizes)
Variant Title: Money Tree - Small
Variant Description: The Money Tree bonsai is known among feng shui enthusiasts to attract the energies of wealth and prosperity. Also known as the “Good Luck Tree,” it features a unique braided trunk that brings charm to wherever it is put on display. Each stem of our ornamental plant features five to seven leaves, creating a delightful radial star pattern. Easy to care for, it’s a perfect gift for bringing good fortune to bonsai experts and novices alike. Braided Money Trees are a popular favorite bonsai. Each trunk stem features five to seven glossy-green plume-like leaves. The bonsai’s trunk has been expertly trained and braided and will continue to grow as plaited. Hardy and exceptionally easy to care for; will thrive in direct sun or low light, with occasional or frequent watering, indoors or out; great for people who travel or don’t have a green thumb. Small Money Tree measures approximately 16-18"H. Arrives in a blue, octagonal ceramic planter with drip holes and matching saucer to catch runoff water.

Variant Product Title: Givenly Branded Box with Choice of Wine or Champagne (Multiple Options)
Variant Title: Givenly Branded Box with Chateau de Sales Pomerol Bordeaux Blend
Variant Description: Pomerol is a much-respected red wine appellation in the Bordeaux region of southwestern France. Both historically and physically, it stands apart from other Bordeaux appellations.  Chateau de Sales, situated in the Right Bank appellation of Pomerol, is an estate with a long and prestigious history. Owned by the same family for over 500 years, the chateau is the largest in Pomerol with 47 hectares of vines. The soil of de Sales is characterized by an omnipresence of iron oxide, called "crasse de fer" locally, which gives the wine a distinct personality. The majority of aging for Chateau de Sales wines takes place in traditional concrete tanks, spending only 6 months in oak barrels, to preserve the wine's qualities of freshness, fruitiness and terroir expression.

Variant Product Title: Givenly Branded Box with Choice of Wine or Champagne (Multiple Options)
Variant Title: Givenly Branded Box with Purple Angel Carmenere
Variant Description: The Super Carmenère of Montes This superb wine represents a whole new dimension for Carmenère, the long-lost grape variety that recently resurfaced in Chile after being presumed extinct in Bordeaux, its original home. In Chile, they consider it their ‘signature’ variety and call it the ‘Jurassic Park’ grape that returned from the past.Montes were pioneers on the Chilean wine scene when they created their super-premium wines: the Montes Alpha range, and icons Montes Alpha M and Montes Folly. Montes also led the way to quality by planting vineyards on steep hillsides. But they also knew when to wait. Aurelio Montes held back on releasing a Carmenère, preferring to take his time and work with the ‘new’ variety until satisfied that his wine would be a top contender, the very best Montes could produce. It was worth the wait: this beauty (a blend of 92% Carmenère and 8% Petit Verdot, aged for 18 months in new French oak barrels) is touched by the wings of an angel … a purple angel!

Variant Product Title: Choice of Wines or Champagnes
Variant Title: Mumm Napa Brut Prestige Sparkling Wine

Brut Prestige features fine bright citrus, red apple, stone fruit and creamy vanilla aromas, with hints of toast, honey and gingerbread spice. Its vibrant flavors are balanced by fine acidity and a rich, lingering finish. 750ml.

Variant Product Title: Choice of Wines or Champagnes
Variant Title: Stag's Leap Winery Chardonnay
Variant Description: The inviting bouquet of this Napa Valley chardonnay expresses aromas of delicate orange blossom, citrus fruits, fresh white peach and subtle hints of sandalwood and cedar (a nod to the well-integrated French Oak) which fill the glass and pique your interest in this crisp Chardonnay. On the palate, you’ll find a refreshingly vibrant Chardonnay with layers of lemon citrus, passion fruit, guava and gooseberry, while also maintaining an elegant roundness in texture that is balanced (hinting at the delicate battonage lees stirring that occurs during the winemaking process). With well-integrated vanilla and caramel oak notes and a flinty minerality on the finish, this wine is full, rich and bright, yet generous in style and maintains freshness due to its acidity, which creates a Chardonnay of lovely complexity and depth. 750ml.

Variant Product Title: Choice of Wines or Champagnes

Variant Product Title: Choice of Wines or Champagnes
Variant Title: Duckhorn Napa Chardonnay
Variant Description: This chardonnay has Inviting aromas of pear, lemongrass, ripe peach, jasmine and graham cracker rise from the glass, revealing this wine’s layered complexity. On the palate, a silky texture creates weight and volume, with elegant acidity framing the stone fruit and citrus flavors. The finish is long and fresh, with tantalizing hints of lemon zest, vanilla and clove. 750ml.

Variant Product Title: Choice of Wines or Champagnes
Variant Title: Cakebread Cellers Chardonnay
Variant Description: This Napa Valley chardonnay has a pretty, floral nose with fresh citrus, orange blossom and white peach, but the real treat is in the mouth. The viscosity coats the palate; it is weighty on the tongue yet well-balanced with acidity. The finish is clean with a nice zing and lingering minerality intertwined with pear and apple lemon.

Variant Product Title: Choice of Wines or Champagnes
Variant Title: Chateau de Sales Pomerol Bordeaux Blend
Variant Description: Pomerol is a much-respected red wine appellation in the Bordeaux region of southwestern France. Both historically and physically, it stands apart from other Bordeaux appellations.  Chateau de Sales, situated in the Right Bank appellation of Pomerol, is an estate with a long and prestigious history. Owned by the same family for over 500 years, the chateau is the largest in Pomerol with 47 hectares of vines. The soil of de Sales is characterized by an omnipresence of iron oxide, called "crasse de fer" locally, which gives the wine a distinct personality. The majority of aging for Chateau de Sales wines takes place in traditional concrete tanks, spending only 6 months in oak barrels, to preserve the wine's qualities of freshness, fruitiness and terroir expression.
Variant Attribute 1: [Choose Wine/Champagne]:Chateau de Sales Pomerol Bordeaux Blend

Variant Title: Duckhorn Paraduxx Proprietary Napa Valley Red Blend
Variant Description: From the only winery devoted to stylish Napa Valley blends, the Paraduxx Proprietary Red Wine is a bold and expressive blend crafted to satisfy the modern palate. It has rich, full fruit flavors and soft, elegant tannins. Composition: 54% Cabernet Sauvignon, 19% Merlot, 16% Zinfandel, 11% Petit Verdot; Oak: 100% French Oak, 40% New Oak and 50% Second Vintage. On the nose, this aromatic wine displays inviting layers of black raspberry and blackberry pie, along with notes of cinnamon stick, vanilla bean and a touch of brown sugar. The lush fruit character continues on the palate where rich currant and cherry flavors are supported by bright acidity and velvety tannins that draw the wine to a silky, berry and spice finish.
Variant Attribute 1: [Choose Wine/Champagne]:Duckhorn Paraduxx Proprietary Napa Valley Red Blend

Variant Product Title: Choice of Wines or Champagnes
Variant Title: Duckhorn Goldeneye Anderson Valley Pinot Noir
Variant Description: Crafted predominantly from our estate vineyards and shaped by the influence of the wind, water and fog, this wine embodies both the elegance of Anderson Valley Pinot Noir, and its deep, rustic beauty.  Varietal Content: 100% Pinot Noir; Cooperage: 100% French Oak Burgundy-style barrels (228 liters), 60% New, 20% Second, 20% Neutral; Medium plus toast: Allier, Vosges and Tronçais Forests.  Combining the lush fruit of our warmer estate vineyards with the rustic elegance of grapes from the cooler “deep end” of the valley, this wine offers a beautifully complete expression of Anderson Valley Pinot Noir. On the palate, lively flavors of wild strawberry and cherry are in perfect harmony, with terroir-driven hints of saddle leather, anise, pennyroyal and wild mushrooms, as well as notes of confectionary spices and vanilla from aging in the finest French oak. 750ml.
Variant Attribute 1: [Choose Wine/Champagne]:Duckhorn Goldeneye Anderson Valley Pinot Noir

Variant Product Title: Choice of Wines or Champagnes
Variant Title: Moet & Chandon Champagne
Variant Description: Moet Imperial is the House’s iconic champagne. Created in 1869, it embodies Moet & Chandon’s unique style, a style distinguished by its bright fruitiness, its seductive palate and its elegant maturity.  Pinot Noir, Pinot Meunier and Chardonnay.  Offers a vibrant intensity of green apple and citrus fruit with the freshness of mineral nuances and white flowers as well as a hint of the elegance of blond  notes (brioche, cereal, fresh nuts).  Taste is of the delicious sumptuousness of white-fleshed fruits (pear, peach, apple) with an alluring caress of fine bubbles. 750ml.

Variant Product Title: Choice of Wines or Champagnes
Variant Title: Jordan Cabernet
Variant Description: Complex and vibrant aromas of red plum, anise, cherry, violets, and tobacco accentuated by notes of black currant, dried herbs, toasted oak, and cocoa. Elegant and supple texture on the palate make the frame for generous flavors of sweet plum and dark cherry, with notes of vanilla and mocha. Silky tannins and well-integrated structure tie together and linger in the finish. 750ml.

Variant Product Title: Choice of Wines or Champagnes
Variant Title: Purple Angel Carmenere
Variant Description: The Super Carmenere of Montes This superb wine represents a whole new dimension for Carmenere, the long-lost grape variety that recently resurfaced in Chile after being presumed extinct in Bordeaux, its original home. In Chile, they consider it their ‘signature’ variety and call it the ‘Jurassic Park’ grape that returned from the past. Montes were pioneers on the Chilean wine scene when they created their super-premium wines: the Montes Alpha range, and icons Montes Alpha M and Montes Folly. Montes also led the way to quality by planting vineyards on steep hillsides. But they also knew when to wait. Aurelio Montes held back on releasing a Carmenere, preferring to take his time and work with the ‘new’ variety until satisfied that his wine would be a top contender, the very best Montes could produce. It was worth the wait: this beauty (a blend of 92% Carmenere and 8% Petit Verdot, aged for 18 months in new French oak barrels) is touched by the wings of an angel … a purple angel!

Variant Product Title: Choice of Wines or Champagnes
Variant Title: Caymus Napa Valley Cabernet
Variant Description: Caymus has a signature style that is dark in color, with rich fruit and ripe, velvety tannins – as approachable in youth as in maturity. Cabernet grapes are farmed in eight of Napa’s 16 sub-appellations, with diversification enabling Caymus to make the best possible wine in a given year.  The Cabernet is an abundant wine in textural tannins yet soft as velvet. Crop thinning, allowing measured sunlight to reach the vine’s fruit zone, extended "hang time"  to wait for increased ripeness are all part of our viticultural practices. Caymus Cabernet offers a wide array of aromas and flavors including cocoa, cassis and vanilla. 750ml.

Variant Product Title: Choice of Wines or Champagnes
Variant Title: Brunello di Montalcino
Variant Description: Brunello di Montalcino is one of Italy's—and the world's—most renowned red wines. Produced in a small zone in southern Tuscany, it is 100% Sangiovese that is released in its fifth year (or later). 750ml.

Variant Product Title: Choice of Wines or Champagnes
Variant Title: Dom Perignon
Variant Description: The quintessential champagne.  The fruit is majestic: ripe, fleshy and profound. Beyond the richness and a certain voluptuousness is a strong impression of consistency that prevails. The wine’s power is remarkably restrained. The various sensations – silky, salty, sappy, bitter and briny – converge and persist. 750ml.

Variant Product Title: Choice of Wines or Champagnes
Variant Title: Louis Roederer Brut Premier Champagne
Variant Description: A great classic that resonates with contemporary taste. Striking a perfect balance between youthfulness and maturity, seduction and character, freshness and vinosity, Brut Premier is a champagne that is harmonious and structured, elegant and lively, with a unique exuberancy. Its structured texture, richness, and length are distinctly winey. It is a full, complex wine that is both rich and powerful, whilst remaining a great classic. 40% Pinot noir, 40% Chardonnay, and 20% Pinot Meunier. 750ml.

Variant Product Title: Choice of Wines or Champagnes
Variant Title: Veuve Clicquot "Yellow Label" Champagne
Variant Description: Veuve Clicquot Yellow Label manages to reconcile two opposing factors - strength and silkiness - and to hold them in perfect balance with aromatic intensity and a lot of freshness. This consistent power to please makes it ideal as an aperitif, and perfect as the Champagne to enjoy with a meal. Traditionally, the proportion of each grape variety used is 50 to 55% Pinot Noir, 15 to 20% Meunier and 28 to 33% Chardonnay. 750ml.

Variant Product Title: Choice of Wines or Champagnes
Variant Title: Duckhorn Napa Cabernet
Variant Description: A classic expression of Napa Valley Cabernet, this wine combines beautiful complexity with rich intensity. Layers of blackberry, huckleberry and black currants are supported by firm, dusty tannins that frame the fruit. On the palate, it is juicy and bright, with luxurious cassis and dark berry flavors supported by notes of fig, cardamom, clove and cracked black pepper that linger on the long, well-structured finish.  86% Cabernet Sauvignon, 8% Merlot, 4% Petit Verdot, 2% Cabernet Franc. 750ml

Variant Product Title: Choice of Wines or Champagnes
Variant Title: Silver Oak Alexander Valley Cabernet
Variant Description: Silver Oak Alexander Valley Cabernet Sauvignon has a garnet color with a ruby red rim and bluish tint. It has an alluring nose of chocolate-covered strawberries, vanilla, nutmeg, truffle and sage. On the palate, it has a broad yet delicate entry and offers cranberry flavors. These flavors are complimented by raspberry and pluot flavors and savory black olive characters on the mid-palate. The wine finishes with silky tannins, cedar and bramble flavors with excellent length and return. 750ml.

Variant Product Title: Choice of Wines or Champagnes
Variant Title: Antinori Tignanello
Variant Description: The 2011 Tignanello is an intense ruby red in color with purple highlights. The wine is ripe on the nose with notes of dark fruit and with much underlying freshness on the aromatic finish; plum fruit dominates the aromatic gamut along with cherries, and the aromas evolve with vigor and balance towards sensations of mint and liquorice. On the palate, though still young, the wine is ready and inviting, rich and harmonious; excellent the balance of the flavors thanks to the tonic acidity and the solidity and suppleness of the tannins. The finish and aftertaste are rich and savory and are characterized by a sweet persistence and length. Tignanello was the first Sangiovese to be aged in barriques, the first contemporary red wine blended with untraditional varieties (specifically Cabernet) and one of the first red wines in the Chianti region region that did not use white grapes. Tignanello is a milestone. It's produced with a selection of Sangiovese, Cabernet Sauvignon and Cabernet Franc.

Variant Product Title: Choice of Wines or Champagnes
Variant Title: Robert Mondavi To Kalon Vineyard Reserve Cabernet Sauvignon
Variant Description: A powerhouse wine, this iconic Cabernet Sauvignon shows the complexity and intensity of our historic To Kalon vineyard, with mouth-filling flavors of fleshy, blackberry, black plum and black currant fruits, savory herbs, black and white pepper, and cardamom spice structured by generous, well-integrated tannins and bright acidity. An iconic, showstopper wine.
Variant Attribute 1: [Choose Wine/Champagne]:Robert Mondavi To Kalon Vineyard Reserve Cabernet Sauvignon

Variant Product Title: Choice of Wines or Champagnes
Variant Title: Quintessa Napa Red Blend
Variant Description: Quintessa is a seductive wine beginning with intense black fruits and warm spice and fi nishing with dense yet silky tannin. Opening with aromas of black cherry and blackcurrant, the wine expands in the glass as notes of clove, bay leaves, and dark chocolate layering on top of crushed rock, graphite and red earth. Fine grained tannin and dense fruit bound together by lively acidity and a long finish complete the picture and promise further pleasure in the years to come. Cabernet Sauvignon, Merlot, Cabernet Franc, Petit Verdot, Carmenere

Variant Product Title: Choice of Wines or Champagnes
Variant Title: Inglenook Rubicon Red Blend
Variant Description: Rubicon demonstrates harmonious, lasting character. Composed this year almost entirely of Cabernet Sauvignon, offers a sweeter, rounder nose than one might find in other vintages, which is a testament to the seamless integration of fruit, tannin, and oak. Weighted throughout, the wine’s fragrance and flavors are linear from start to finish, with sophisticated notes of dark berries, black cherries, currants, spice and vanilla flowing together, bringing impressive complexity to this outstanding vintage. 97% Cabernet Sauvignon, 2%Merlot, 1% Petit Verdot 750ml

Variant Product Title: Choice of Wines or Champagnes
Variant Title: Joseph Phelps Insignia
Variant Description: Insignia is densely hued with rich dark fruit, cocoa powder and fragrant dried flower notes. Velvety texture and weight on the palate with layers of juicy black plum, Madagascar vanilla and bergamot. Bold, creamy and supple with integrated tannin structure and a lengthy finish. 90% Cabernet Sauvignon, 7% Petit Verdot, 2% Cabernet Franc and 1% Malbec from estate-grown Napa Valley vineyards. 750ml.

Variant Product Title: Choice of Wines or Champagnes
Variant Title: Etude Pinot Noir BGR 2016 Carneros
Variant Description: The Etude Carneros Estate vineyard, Grace Benoist Ranch, boasts some of the best fruit in the appellation for both Pinot Noir and Chardonnay.A vibrant red ruby color, this 2016 Carneros Pinot Noir shows lifted red berry fruit flavors and aromas of fresh strawberry, Bing cherry, and raspberry, along with the signature cinnamon graham cracker spice found in our Grace Benoist Ranch Pinots Noirs. Appealing and bright, concentrated red fruit comes through on the palate, alongside delicate mineral earth and spice notes, followed by a lush mouthfeel and silky tannins. Youthful and fresh but with the potential to age for up to 10 years. 750ml.

Variant Product Title: Choice of Liquor
Variant Title: Woodford Reserve Whiskey
Variant Description:
Rich, chewy, rounded and smooth, with complex citrus, cinnamon and cocoa.
Toffee, caramel, chocolate and spice notes abound. Finishes silky smooth, almost creamy at first with a long, warm satisfying tail. 90.4 proof.  750ml

Variant Product Title: Choice of Liquor
Variant Title: Jameson Irish Whiskey
Variant Description: The perfect balance of spicy, nutty and vanilla notes with hints of sweet sherry and exceptional smoothness. A light floral fragrance, peppered with spicy wood and sweet notes.  Triple distilled and aged a minimum of 4 years. 80 proof.  750ml

Variant Product Title: Choice of Liquor
Variant Title: Bookers Bourbon
Variant Description: Beautiful color that is a deep chestnut and has a robust and flavor rich taste profile.  The nose is a rich balance of vanilla and oak that comes from aging in the white oak barrels for over six years.  The finish is balanced and pleasant and does not overpower your taste buds. 126 proof. 750ml.

Variant Product Title: Choice of Liquor
Variant Title: Crown Royal Whiskey
Variant Description: Cloying caramel, citrus, vanilla, fruit and a doughy caky quality mix and mingle with a watery sweetness and maple syrup while a brooding raw grain haunts the background.  Finishes with a hint of caramel syrup, vanilla, candy corn, watery maple and raw grain bleed out in a long slow finish. 80 proof. 750ml.

Variant Product Title: Choice of Liquor
Variant Title: Macallan 10 year Scotch
Variant Description: A crisp whiskey. The fruit comes across more tropical but a good dose of orchard fruit is also mixed in. Cinnamon, vanilla, malt, raisins and dark fruit notes layer in with a wee bit of wood and a marzipan style sweetness that is laying beneath the complex fruit notes. It’s a great taste indeed. Finishes with a fruity kick and dominates the medium finish and blends with notes of vanilla, wood, spice, malt and a feint ash. 100 proof.

Variant Product Title: Choice of Liquor
Variant Title: Macallan 15 year Scotch
Variant Description: Single malt whisky triple aged in American and European sherry and bourbon oak. Starts smooth and sweet like thinned maple syrup but that turns woody, green and piney but all these are not overdone. There is a small amount of char smoke, maple syrup, and vanilla cream as you continue and a dash of spice on the finish.  86 proof.  750ml.

Variant Product Title: Choice of Liquor
Variant Title: Glenlivet 12 year Scotch
Variant Description: One of the most famous malts in the world. Glenlivet 12yo has a soft smooth balance of sweet summer fruits and the floral notes of spring flowers.  Delicately balanced with strong pineapple notes. 80 proof. 750ml.

Variant Product Title: Choice of Liquor
Variant Title: Skyy Vodka
Variant Description: SKYY is one of the first vodkas made from American grains and water, and uses an innovative proprietary quadruple distillation and triple filtration process. SKYY’s proprietary process delivers a dry, medium body with nice creamy mouth feel, and anise & coriander notes with a faint peppery finish.  80 proof.  750ml.

Variant Product Title: Choice of Liquor
Variant Title: Titos Handmade Vodka
Variant Description: Offers a slightly sweet, peppery scent on the nose, then coats the palate with a creamy body, finishing nice and smooth, leaving a hint of sweet corn and spice.  80 Proof. 750ml. Presented in a rustic wooden wine gift crate engraved with your logo. Box dimension is 14" x 4.5" x 4.5."

Variant Product Title: Choice of Liquor
Variant Title: Patron Silver Tequila
Variant Description: Boutique premium blanco tequila from one of the most famous houses in Mexico, this is a fine white tequila with good purity of flavor. Crisp clean flavors of citrus and oak are present in the nose followed by a full finish on the palate. 80 proof.  750ml.

Variant Product Title: Choice of Liquor
Variant Title: Casamigos Blanco Tequila
Variant Description: Produced from the finest hand selected, 100% Blue Weber Agave which is grown in the rich, red clay and cool climate of Jalisco Highlands of Mexico. Variant Product Title: Choice of Liquor
Variant Title: Sailor Jerry Spiced Rum
Variant Description: Vanilla spice, butter, oak, cinnamon, nutmeg and ground ginger. Drying and sweet on the palate with notes of winter spice and black pepper, toffee. Makes an incredible spiced mojito. 92 proof. 750ml.

Variant Product Title: Choice of Liquor
Variant Title: Hendrick's Gin
Variant Description: Hendrick's Gin is infused with the curious, yet marvellous, essences of rose and cucumber, delectably supported by no less than 11 botanicals from the four corners of the world. This whimsical concoction produces a wonderfully refreshing gin with a delightfully floral aroma.  88 proof.  750ml.

Variant Product Title: Choice of Liquor
Variant Title: Bombay Sapphire Gin
Variant Description: Bombay Sapphire opens with a touch of juniper, a ripe citrus and hints of spice in the fragrance. The palate is exceptionally smooth and allows the botanicals to open up one by one and mix in the most lovely way with juniper slightly at the forefront. The finish is bolder but retains the spirit's brightness. 94 proof. 750ml.

Variant Product Title: Choice of Liquor
Variant Title: Bailey's Irish Cream
Variant Description: Bailey’s, the first Irish cream liqueur on the market, has earned the place it now has in almost every bar in the world. Creamy and nutty, with cocoa bean and chocolate notes, this liqueur is perfect for so many occasions. Don’t forget to pour it on your ice cream for dessert. 34 proof.  750ml.

Variant Product Title: Choice of 2 Wine Set
Variant Title: Coppola Diamond Cabernet & Coppola Diamond Chardonnay

The Diamond Chardonnay reflects the distinctive personality of Monterey vineyards, which give rise to juicy apple, guava and melon flavors.  Whole-cluster pressing and a combination of barrel and stainless steel fermentation ensures that the creamy texture and caramelized sugar finish is balanced by a crisp acidity. 750ml.

With well-integrated vanilla and caramel oak notes and a flinty minerality on the finish, this wine is full, rich and bright, yet generous in style and maintains freshness due to its acidity, which creates a Chardonnay of lovely complexity and depth. 750ml.
